        "name": "Muskoka Wharf & RMS Segwun",
        "stop": "Gravenhurst",
        "category": "Nature",
        "desc": "The heart of Gravenhurst's waterfront and one of Muskoka's most iconic attractions. Step aboard the RMS Segwun — the oldest coal-fired steamship in North America still in operation, launched in 1887. Scenic cruises on Lake Muskoka depart from the Muskoka Wharf throughout the summer season. The Discovery Centre tells the story of the steamship era. Waterfront restaurants, shops, the Tall Pines Music Festival, and Dockside Festival all call the Wharf home. A short walk from Gravenhurst station.",
